---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About Us | Property App 2026" description="Why Property App exists and what standard it is trying to raise for property search and listing management in Southeast Asia.">
  <section class="about-hero card">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <span class="pill">About Property App</span>
      <h1>We are trying to make property search and listing management feel clearer, safer, and more accountable.</h1>
      <p>
        Too many property portals in the region still feel like noisy directories. Buyers get overloaded, owners get low-quality leads, and trust is treated as a marketing layer instead of a product system. We are building a marketplace that behaves more like a real workflow.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-grid section-gap">
    <article class="card about-card">
      <strong>The problem we care about</strong>
      <p>
        Buyers and renters should be able to search with context, compare a few serious options, and contact with confidence. Owners should be able to publish with structure, manage responses, and understand whether a listing is actually performing.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card about-card">
      <strong>The standard we are aiming for</strong>
      <p>
        Better search quality, stronger trust signals, cleaner listing operations, and product flows that help people decide rather than just click around.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="market-band card section-gap">
    <div>
      <span class="pill">Where we operate</span>
      <h2>We are building for the Southeast Asian property market, where large portals and large advisory brands already prove the demand exists.</h2>
      <p>
        The region already supports broad search operators, local classifieds-style portals, and premium sales advisers. That matters because the market is large. It also matters because users already know what the old model feels like, and many of those products still feel heavier, older, or more fragmented than they should.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="belief-grid">
      <article>
        <strong>Portal operators</strong>
        <span>Examples in-market show strong search breadth, directory depth, and localisation basics. They prove inventory demand, but often still feel cluttered and operationally thin.</span>
      </article>
      <article>
        <strong>Premium advisers</strong>
        <span>Brands like Savills show there is real premium demand and serious supply in the region. They prove the high-end market exists, but they do not solve the broader product workflow problem on their own.</span>
      </article>
      <article>
        <strong>What this means for us</strong>
        <span>We should serve both everyday and premium users without falling back to either a noisy portal or a purely brokerage-led experience.</span>
      </article>
      <article>
        <strong>The standard we are building toward</strong>
        <span>Search that feels modern, operations that feel responsive, trust that feels visible, and personal support when automation is not enough.</span>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mission-band card section-gap">
    <div>
      <span class="pill">What we believe</span>
      <h2>A strong marketplace is not just a big inventory count.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="belief-grid">
      <article>
        <strong>Clarity over clutter</strong>
        <span>Search, shortlist, compare, and enquiry should feel connected instead of fragmented.</span>
      </article>
      <article>
        <strong>Trust over empty claims</strong>
        <span>Verification, reporting, and visible process matter more than broad platform promises.</span>
      </article>
      <article>
        <strong>Decision support over noise</strong>
        <span>Buyers need help narrowing choices, not more reasons to hesitate.</span>
      </article>
      <article>
        <strong>Operations over vanity</strong>
        <span>Owners need feedback, billing clarity, and enquiry handling that actually helps them act.</span>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-grid section-gap">
    <a class="card cta-card" href="/why-property-app">
      <span class="pill">Why us</span>
      <strong>See what should make this stand out</strong>
      <p>Understand the product differences we think matter in this market.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card cta-card" href="/trust">
      <span class="pill">Trust and safety</span>
      <strong>See how protection is built into the product</strong>
      <p>Read how verification, reporting, and structured workflows support safer use.</p>
    </a>
  </section>

  <style is:inline>
    .about-hero,
    .market-band,
    .about-card,
    .mission-band,
    .cta-card {
      padding: 1.4rem;
    }
    .about-hero {
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.1), transparent 26rem),
        linear-gradient(180deg, var(--surface-overlay-strong), var(--surface-panel-muted));
    }
    .hero-copy,
    .mission-band,
    .market-band {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.9rem;
    }
    .about-hero h1,
    .mission-band h2,
    .market-band h2 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
      line-height: 0.95;
      letter-spacing: -0.08em;
      max-width: 13ch;
    }
    .about-hero p,
    .about-card p,
    .market-band p,
    .belief-grid span,
    .cta-card p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.72;
    }
    .about-grid,
    .belief-grid,
    .cta-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
    }
    .about-card,
    .belief-grid article,
    .cta-card {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.45rem;
      background: var(--surface-overlay);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      text-decoration: none;
      color: inherit;
    }
    .about-card strong,
    .belief-grid strong,
    .cta-card strong {
      font-size: 1rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }
    @media (max-width: 860px) {
      .about-grid,
      .belief-grid,
      .cta-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
